```sql
/* Get AGN objects with r-band variability but no g-band variability/detections */
WITH agn_objects AS (
    SELECT p.oid, p.probability
    FROM probability p
    WHERE p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'
    AND p.ranking = 1
    AND p.class_name = 'AGN'
),
r_band_var AS (
    SELECT m.oid
    FROM magstat m
    INNER JOIN agn_objects a ON m.oid = a.oid
    WHERE m.fid = 2  /* r band */
    AND m.ndet > 0
    AND m.magsigma_corr > 0
),
g_band_nonvar AS (
    SELECT m.oid
    FROM magstat m
    INNER JOIN agn_objects a ON m.oid = a.oid
    WHERE m.fid = 1  /* g band */
    AND (m.ndet = 0 OR m.magsigma_corr = 0)
)
SELECT o.*, p.probability, 
       mg.ndet as g_ndet, mg.magsigma_corr as g_sigma,
       mr.ndet as r_ndet, mr.magsigma_corr as r_sigma
FROM object o
INNER JOIN agn_objects p ON o.oid = p.oid
INNER JOIN r_band_var r ON o.oid = r.oid
INNER JOIN g_band_nonvar g ON o.oid = g.oid
INNER JOIN magstat mg ON o.oid = mg.oid AND mg.fid = 1
INNER JOIN magstat mr ON o.oid = mr.oid AND mr.fid = 2
ORDER BY o.oid ASC;
```

```sql
/* First get AGN objects with required probability and time coverage */
WITH agn_objects AS (
    SELECT o.*, p.probability
    FROM probability p
    INNER JOIN object o ON o.oid = p.oid
    WHERE p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'
    AND p.class_name = 'AGN'
    AND p.probability > 0.6
    AND p.ranking = 1
    AND o.deltajd >= 365.25
    AND o.ndet >= 20
),
/* Get magnitude statistics per band */
mag_stats AS (
    SELECT m.oid,
           m.fid AS magstat_fid,
           m.magmax_corr,
           m.magmin_corr,
           (m.magmax_corr - m.magmin_corr) AS delta_mag
    FROM magstat m
    INNER JOIN agn_objects a ON a.oid = m.oid
    WHERE (m.fid = 1 AND (m.magmax_corr - m.magmin_corr) > 1.0) /* g band variation > 1.0 */
       OR (m.fid = 2 AND (m.magmax_corr - m.magmin_corr) > 0.5) /* r band variation > 0.5 */
)
/* Final selection combining all conditions */
SELECT DISTINCT 
    a.oid,
    a.meanra,
    a.meandec,
    a.ndet,
    m.magstat_fid,
    m.magmax_corr,
    m.magmin_corr,
    m.delta_mag
FROM agn_objects a
INNER JOIN mag_stats m ON a.oid = m.oid
/* Ensure object has variations in both bands */
WHERE EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 
    FROM mag_stats m2 
    WHERE m2.oid = a.oid 
    AND m2.magstat_fid = 1
    AND m2.delta_mag > 1.0
)
AND EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 
    FROM mag_stats m3 
    WHERE m3.oid = a.oid 
    AND m3.magstat_fid = 2
    AND m3.delta_mag > 0.5
)
ORDER BY a.oid, m.magstat_fid
```

```sql
/* First get AGN objects with probability > 0.6 */
WITH agn_objects AS (
    SELECT p.oid, p.probability
    FROM probability p
    WHERE p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'
    AND p.class_name = 'AGN'
    AND p.probability > 0.6
    AND p.ranking = 1
),
/* Join with object table to get time coverage and detection requirements */
filtered_objects AS (
    SELECT a.oid, o.meanra, o.meandec, o.ndet
    FROM agn_objects a
    INNER JOIN object o ON a.oid = o.oid
    WHERE o.deltajd >= 365.25 
    AND o.ndet >= 20
),
/* Get magnitude statistics per band */
mag_stats AS (
    SELECT 
        m.oid,
        m.fid AS magstat_fid,
        m.magmax_corr,
        m.magmin_corr,
        (m.magmax_corr - m.magmin_corr) as delta_mag
    FROM magstat m
    WHERE m.corrected = true
    AND (
        (m.fid = 1 AND (m.magmax_corr - m.magmin_corr) > 1.0) OR
        (m.fid = 2 AND (m.magmax_corr - m.magmin_corr) > 0.5)
    )
)
/* Final selection joining all conditions */
SELECT DISTINCT
    f.oid,
    f.meanra,
    f.meandec,
    f.ndet,
    m.magstat_fid,
    m.magmax_corr,
    m.magmin_corr,
    m.delta_mag,
    p.probability
FROM filtered_objects f
INNER JOIN mag_stats m ON f.oid = m.oid
INNER JOIN agn_objects p ON f.oid = p.oid
ORDER BY f.oid, m.magstat_fid;
```

```sql
/* Get AGN objects with high probability and required detections */
WITH agn_objects AS (
    SELECT p.oid, o.meanra, o.meandec, o.ndet
    FROM probability p
    INNER JOIN object o ON p.oid = o.oid
    WHERE p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'
    AND p.class_name = 'AGN'
    AND p.probability > 0.6
    AND p.ranking = 1
    AND o.deltajd >= 365.25
    AND o.ndet >= 20
),
/* Get magnitude statistics per band */
mag_stats AS (
    SELECT 
        oid,
        fid AS magstat_fid,
        magmax_corr,
        magmin_corr,
        (magmax_corr - magmin_corr) AS delta_mag
    FROM magstat
    WHERE corrected = true
    AND (
        (fid = 1 AND (magmax_corr - magmin_corr) > 1.0) OR
        (fid = 2 AND (magmax_corr - magmin_corr) > 0.5)
    )
)
/* Combine results and apply final filters */
SELECT DISTINCT
    a.oid,
    a.meanra,
    a.meandec,
    a.ndet,
    m.magstat_fid,
    m.magmax_corr,
    m.magmin_corr,
    m.delta_mag
FROM agn_objects a
INNER JOIN mag_stats m ON a.oid = m.oid
WHERE EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 FROM mag_stats m1 
    WHERE m1.oid = a.oid 
    AND m1.magstat_fid = 1 
    AND m1.delta_mag > 1.0
)
AND EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 FROM mag_stats m2 
    WHERE m2.oid = a.oid 
    AND m2.magstat_fid = 2 
    AND m2.delta_mag > 0.5
)
ORDER BY a.oid, m.magstat_fid;
```

```sql
/* Get SNe from stamp classifier with first detection in September 1-2 and fast risers */
WITH sn_candidates AS (
    SELECT p.oid, p.probability
    FROM probability p
    WHERE p.classifier_name = 'stamp_classifier'
    AND p.class_name = 'SN'
    AND p.ranking = 1
),
fast_risers AS (
    SELECT o.oid, sc.probability, m.fid as magstat_fid, m.dmdt_first
    FROM object o
    INNER JOIN sn_candidates sc ON o.oid = sc.oid
    INNER JOIN magstat m ON o.oid = m.oid
    WHERE o.firstmjd BETWEEN 60188.0 AND 60189.0
    AND m.dmdt_first >= 0.25
),
light_curves AS (
    SELECT fr.*, d.fid, d.diffmaglim
    FROM fast_risers fr
    INNER JOIN detection d ON fr.oid = d.oid
)
SELECT *
FROM light_curves
ORDER BY oid
LIMIT 100;
```

```sql
)
```

```sql
    p.probability
FROM (
    /* First filter detections by g band and count them per object */
    SELECT 
        oid,
        COUNT(*) as det_count
    FROM detection
    WHERE fid = 1  /* g band */
        AND dubious = FALSE
    GROUP BY oid
    HAVING COUNT(*) >= 10
) d
INNER JOIN probability p ON d.oid = p.oid
WHERE p.ranking = 1
    AND p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'
ORDER BY d.oid
LIMIT 500;
```

```sql
/* Get CV/Nova objects with their detections and magnitude information */
WITH base_objects AS (
    SELECT p.oid
    FROM probability p
    INNER JOIN object o ON p.oid = o.oid
    WHERE p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier_stochastic'
    AND p.class_name = 'CV/Nova'
    AND p.ranking = 1
    AND o.ndet <= 50
),
min_mags AS (
    SELECT d.oid,
           MIN(d.magpsf_corr) as min_mag
    FROM detection d
    INNER JOIN base_objects b ON d.oid = b.oid
    WHERE d.fid = 2 
    AND d.corrected = true
    GROUP BY d.oid
)
SELECT DISTINCT d.oid,
       d.candid,
       d.fid AS f_id,
       d.ra,
       d.dec,
       d.magpsf,
       d.sigmapsf,
       d.magpsf_corr,
       d.sigmapsf_corr,
       (d.magpsf_corr - m.min_mag) as rise_from_min
FROM detection d
INNER JOIN base_objects b ON d.oid = b.oid
INNER JOIN min_mags m ON d.oid = m.oid
WHERE d.fid = 2
AND d.corrected = true
ORDER BY d.oid
LIMIT 1000;
```

```sql
/* Get CV/Nova objects with their detections and magnitude information */
WITH base_objects AS (
    SELECT p.oid
    FROM probability p
    INNER JOIN object o ON p.oid = o.oid
    WHERE p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier_stochastic'
    AND p.class_name = 'CV/Nova'

),

           d.ra,
           d.dec, 
           d.magpsf,
           d.sigmapsf,
           d.magpsf_corr,
           d.sigmapsf_corr,
           MAX(d.magpsf_corr) OVER (PARTITION BY d.oid) - MIN(d.magpsf_corr) OVER (PARTITION BY d.oid) as max_rise
    FROM detection d
    INNER JOIN base_objects b ON d.oid = b.oid
    WHERE d.fid = 2 /* r-band */
    AND d.corrected = true
)
SELECT *
FROM mag_info
ORDER BY oid
LIMIT 1000;
```
